{"id":"math120-lineval-fg001","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Functions and Graphs","subtopic":"Evaluating functions","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A company's revenue is modeled by R(x) = {m}x + {b}, where x is units sold. Find R({x_val}).","params":{"m":{"type":"int","min":10,"max":50},"b":{"type":"int","min":100,"max":500},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":5,"max":20}},"answer_expr":"lineval","steps":["Substitute x = {x_val}: R({x_val}) = {m}({x_val}) + {b}.","= {m_times_x} + {b} = {answer_lineval}."],"tags":["survey-calculus","functions","linear","business"]}
